  "response_text": "Here is a balanced and healthy 3-day meal plan designed to provide sustained energy, essential nutrients, and variety. It focuses on whole foods, lean proteins, healthy fats, and complex carbohydrates.\n\n**General Guidelines:**\n- **Hydration:** Drink plenty of water (8+ glasses/day). Herbal tea is also great.\n- **Portions:** Adjust portion sizes based on your individual activity level and hunger cues.\n- **Cooking:** Use healthy cooking methods like baking, grilling, steaming, or sautéing with olive or avocado oil.\n- **Snacks:** If hungry between meals, choose from: a piece of fruit, a small handful of nuts, plain yogurt, or raw vegetables with hummus.\n\n---\n\n### Day 1\n\n**Breakfast (approx. 350 calories)**\n- **Overnight Oats:** 1/2 cup rolled oats, 1 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 tbsp chia seeds, 1/2 cup mixed berries. Mix in a jar and refrigerate overnight. Top with 1 tbsp chopped almonds before eating.\n\n**Lunch (approx. 450 calories)**\n- **Grilled Chicken Salad:** 4 oz grilled chicken breast (sliced), over a large bed of mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, bell peppers, and 1/4 avocado. Dressing: 2 tbsp olive oil + 1 tbsp lemon juice + salt & pepper.\n\n**Dinner (approx. 500 calories)**\n- **Baked Salmon with Roasted Veggies:** 5 oz salmon fillet (seasoned with dill, lemon, garlic). Roast at 400°F (200°C) for 12-15 minutes. Serve with 1 cup roasted broccoli and 1/2 cup cooked quinoa.\n\n---\n\n### Day 2\n\n**Breakfast (approx. 300 calories)**\n- **Greek Yogurt Bowl:** 1 cup plain Greek yogurt (2% or full fat). Top with 1/2 cup sliced strawberries, 1 tbsp flaxseed meal, and 1 tbsp chopped walnuts.\n\n**Lunch (approx. 450 calories)**\n- **Lentil & Vegetable Soup:** 2 cups homemade or low-sodium lentil soup (with carrots, celery, onions, spinach). Serve with a small whole-grain roll or a side salad with vinaigrette.\n\n**Dinner (approx. 500 calories)**\n- **Turkey & Vegetable Stir-fry:** 4 oz lean ground turkey, cooked with 2 cups mixed stir-fry vegetables (bell peppers, snap peas, bok choy, carrots). Sauce: 2 tbsp low-sodium soy sauce, 1 tsp sesame oil, minced garlic & ginger. Serve over 1/2 cup cooked brown rice.\n\n---\n\n### Day 3\n\n**Breakfast (approx. 350 calories)**\n- **Scrambled Eggs with Veggies:** 2 large eggs scrambled with 1 cup spinach, 1/4 cup diced tomatoes, and 1/4 cup chopped mushrooms. Cook in 1 tsp olive oil. Serve with 1 slice of whole-grain toast.\n\n**Lunch (approx. 450 calories)**\n- **Quinoa & Black Bean Bowl:** 1 cup cooked quinoa, 1/2 cup black beans (rinsed), 1/2 cup corn, diced red bell pepper, chopped cilantro. Dressing: lime juice + a pinch of cumin + olive oil. Top with 1/4 avocado.\n\n**Dinner (approx. 500 calories)**\n- **Grilled Shrimp & Zucchini Noodles:** 5 oz grilled shrimp (seasoned with paprika & garlic). Sauté 2 cups spiralized zucchini (\"zoodles\") for 2 minutes with a little olive oil and cherry tomatoes. Top with fresh basil and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese (optional).\n\n---\n\n### Optional Healthy Snacks (100-150 calories each)\n- Apple slices with 1 tbsp peanut butter.\n- 1/2 cup cottage cheese with black pepper.\n- A small handful of almonds (about 12-15).\n- 1 hard-boiled egg.\n- Celery sticks with 2 tbsp hummus.\n\n**Important Note:** This is a sample plan. For personalized advice, especially if you have specific health conditions, allergies, or dietary restrictions, please consult a registered dietitian or healthcare provider.",
